<%- layout("layouts/boilerplate") %>

<div class="hosting-responsibly-page">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="hero-section">
      <h1>Hosting responsibly</h1>
      <p class="lead">Being a good host means being a good neighbour</p>
      <p>Hosting comes with a commitment to neighbours and to the community. Here's how to be a responsible host.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-8">
        <h2>Be a good neighbour</h2>
        <p>Successful hosting is about more than just welcoming guests—it's about being part of your community.</p>
        
        <div class="responsibility-cards">
          <div class="responsibility-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-users"></i> Respect your neighbours</h3>
            <p>Let your neighbours know you're hosting and provide them with your contact information for any concerns.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="responsibility-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-volume-mute"></i> Manage noise levels</h3>
            <p>Set clear house rules about quiet hours and noise to avoid disturbing neighbours.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="responsibility-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-parking"></i> Parking considerations</h3>
            <p>Inform guests about parking rules and ensure they don't block driveways or reserved spaces.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="responsibility-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-trash-alt"></i> Waste management</h3>
            <p>Provide clear instructions for trash disposal and ensure guests follow local waste regulations.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2>Follow local regulations</h2>
        <p>Understand and comply with all local laws and regulations related to short-term rentals.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Rental registration requirements</li>
          <li>Zoning laws and restrictions</li>
          <li>Occupancy limits</li>
          <li>Tax obligations</li>
          <li>Safety and building codes</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Provide accurate information</h2>
        <p>Be honest and transparent in your listing to set proper expectations for guests.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Accurate photos and descriptions</li>
          <li>Clear house rules</li>
          <li>Honest amenity listings</li>
          <li>Transparent pricing</li>
          <li>Accurate location information</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Communicate clearly with guests</h2>
        <p>Good communication helps prevent issues and ensures a positive experience for everyone.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Respond promptly to inquiries</li>
          <li>Provide detailed check-in instructions</li>
          <li>Share house rules before booking</li>
          <li>Be available for questions during stays</li>
          <li>Provide local recommendations</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Ensure guest safety</h2>
        <p>Take steps to ensure your guests have a safe and comfortable stay.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Working smoke and carbon monoxide detectors</li>
          <li>Fire extinguishers</li>
          <li>First aid kit</li>
          <li>Emergency contact information</li>
          <li>Secure locks and entry systems</li>
          <li>Clear evacuation routes</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Practice non-discrimination</h2>
        <p>Treat all guests equally and fairly. Discrimination is never acceptable on Wanderlust.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Accept guests regardless of race, religion, disability, or other protected characteristics</li>
          <li>Provide equal service to all guests</li>
          <li>Follow our Nondiscrimination Policy</li>
          <li>Report any discrimination you witness</li>
        </ul>
        <a href="/anti-discrimination" class="btn-link">Learn about our Nondiscrimination Policy →</a>

        <h2>Community Disturbance Policy</h2>
        <p>Our Community Disturbance Policy outlines expectations for hosts and guests to maintain good relationships with neighbours.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>No parties or events without prior approval</li>
          <li>Respect quiet hours</li>
          <li>Limit the number of guests to your listing capacity</li>
          <li>Address neighbour concerns promptly</li>
        </ul>
        <a href="#" class="btn-link">Read the Community Disturbance Policy →</a>
      </div>
      
      <div class="col-md-4">
        <div class="sidebar-card">
          <h3>Quick links</h3>
          <ul class="sidebar-links">
            <li><a href="/anti-discrimination">Nondiscrimination Policy</a></li>
            <li><a href="/report-neighbourhood-concern">Report neighbourhood concern</a></li>
            <li><a href="/hosting-resources">Hosting resources</a></li>
            <li><a href="/community-forum">Community forum</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="sidebar-card mt-4">
          <h3>Need help?</h3>
          <p>If you have questions about responsible hosting, our support team is here to help.</p>
          <a href="/helpcenter" class="btn btn-outline-primary btn-block">Contact Support</a>
        </div>

        <div class="sidebar-card mt-4">
          <h3>Learn from others</h3>
          <p>Join the community forum to connect with other hosts and share best practices.</p>
          <a href="/community-forum" class="btn btn-outline-primary btn-block">Visit Community forum</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
